INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('873', '1', '2013-12-26 07:20:50', '2013-12-26 07:20:50', '<div>\r\n\r\nWhile most people living in Maryland and beyond understand how serious brain injuries can be, fewer may realize just how vulnerable they can be to sustaining such injuries. It seems that traumatic brain injuries are finally gaining the attention and research they deserve, and experts are beginning to understand the full scale of complexities and dangers associated with head trauma. One major development in regards to addressing the needs and long-term care of accident victims is recognizing that even seemingly minor accidents can have potentially life altering effects on victims.\r\n\r\nMedical researchers and experts are beginning to note that some medical conditions commonly related to factors like age may actually be the latent manifestations of previous brain injuries. At the same time, experts now suspect there may be a link between some low-speed car accident incidents and traumatic brain injury cases. In collisions that occur at speeds below 20 miles per hour, the occupant of the vehicle (not the vehicle itself) sustains the impact of the crash. Consequently, even victims of a minor car accident can suffer everything from spinal damage to brain damage to serious whiplash. The issue, then, may be to correctly identify and treat brain injuries following minor accidents.\r\n\r\nSome car accident victims may be tempted to underestimate and/or ignore some brain injury symptoms, especially if they present themselves weeks after the initial incident occurred. It’s very important, though, that individuals be aware of symptoms like headaches, depression, unusual mood changes and memory loss. These and other symptoms may not appear for weeks and can result from minor collisions.\r\n\r\n<b>Source: </b>legalexaminer.com, “<a href=\"http://lansing.legalexaminer.com/automobile-accidents/low-speed-collisions-and-traumatic-brain-injuries-part-i/\" target=\"_blank\">Low Speed Collisions and Traumatic Brain Injuries: Part I</a>,” David Mittleman, December 10, 2013.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Even minor accident victims can sustain brain damage', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'even-minor-accident-victims-can-sustain-brain-damage', '', '', '2014-02-28 07:21:59', '2014-02-28 07:21:59', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=873', '0', 'post', '', '0');
