INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('880', '1', '2013-07-29 07:28:32', '2013-07-29 07:28:32', '<div>\r\n\r\nIt is important for Maryland doctors to carefully review their patients’ medical records and to communicate potential risks with their colleagues. Failure to do so could result in grave medical errors that lead to serious brain injury.\r\n\r\nSoon after a girl was born, she had a heart transplant that enabled her to lead a healthy, normal life. However, when the girl was 4 years old, she developed a cold. When the girl’s mother called the hospital for instructions, the doctor allegedly recommended that she give Afrin to the child, despite warnings from the child’s cardiologist.\r\n\r\nFor an unknown reason, the doctor had dismissed the cardiologist’s orders. When the girl’s mother gave Afrin to the girl, it apparently put additional strain on her heart, and she stopped breathing. Ultimately, it caused severe brain damage, and the girl, who is now 8 years old, has not been the same since, and it is likely that her condition is permanent. According to the girl’s mother, she now requires constant care. Even though the hospital alleges that Afrin did not cause the girl’s brain damage, the judge ruled in favor of the girl’s family. The hospital, which continues to treat the girl, awarded $15.2 million to the family.\r\n\r\nEspecially when the victim is a child, brain injuries are devastating for the victim’s family members. Fortunately, the accident compensation that the victim’s family received will enable them to cover the child’s medical expenses. People in similar situations may want to talk to a personal injury attorney about their case.\r\n\r\n<b>Source: </b><strong>Source: </strong>KIRO TV, “<a href=\"http://www.kirotv.com/news/news/judge-awards-152-million-girl-brain-damage-after-h/nYpDp/\" target=\"_blank\">Judge awards $15.2 million for girl with brain damage after hospital error</a>,” Amy Clancy, July 12, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Hospital pays $15.2 million to brain injury victim', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hospital-pays-15-2-million-to-brain-injury-victim', '', '', '2014-02-28 07:29:32', '2014-02-28 07:29:32', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=880', '0', 'post', '', '0');
