INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('896', '1', '2013-05-24 07:40:28', '2013-05-24 07:40:28', '<div>\r\n\r\nWith the beginning of summer, Maryland residents and property owners need to take special precautions that will keep people safe on their property. There’s nothing wrong with enjoying fun summer activities, but it’s important to remember that with one small mistake, someone’s life can be changed forever. And if an accident happened on your property, you could be held responsible for the medical expenses of someone who was injured, and possibly even face criminal or negligence charges.\r\n\r\nChildren are especially vulnerable to injuries or worse with many of the summer activities the rest of us take for granted. Swimming pools are a great source of danger for kids who can’t swim, and even for some who can. Some residences don’t have their backyard pools fenced or locked up, and this can be very dangerous to child visitors as well as residents.\r\n\r\nTragically, a 3-year-old Tucson girl drowned in a backyard swimming pool last week during a gathering of friends and family at a residence. Authorities say there were several adults and older children present in the home, and people had not seen the little girl for 15 minutes before she was discovered in the pool shortly before midnight. After pulling the child from the pool, adults received CPR instructions from 911 operators until paramedics arrived. Sadly, efforts to save the little girl at a local hospital were unsuccessful.\r\n\r\nThe backyard pool didn’t have a fence to keep non-swimmers away. The Sheriff’s Department is investigating the accident, but it’s unknown at this time whether there will be any charges. It’s possible the child’s parents could pursue a lawsuit against the owners of the home. Because child drownings are an unfortunate occurrence every summer in residential properties across the country, it’s crucial for homeowners to take safety precautions to protect children.\r\n\r\n<b>Source: </b>KVOA.com, “<a href=\"http://www.kvoa.com/news/3-year-old-drowns-in-backyard-pool/#_\" target=\"_blank\">3-year-old drowns in backyard pool</a>,” Scott Oathout, May 6, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Adult carelessness can lead to summer tragedies', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'adult-carelessness-can-lead-to-summer-tragedies', '', '', '2014-02-28 07:41:37', '2014-02-28 07:41:37', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=896', '0', 'post', '', '0');
