INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('902', '1', '2013-02-21 07:44:30', '2013-02-21 07:44:30', '<div>\r\n\r\nWe\'ve all had moments where we\'ve wished parents would control their children in public places. Not only are they an annoyance to others, but out-of-control kids can pose a danger to themselves and other people. Most businesses have policies in place that require parents to supervise their children while shopping. This prevents them or other customers from getting hurt by merchandise, hot foods or liquids or damaging property.\r\n\r\nIn some instances, the parents are unable to supervise or correct their misbehaving children. Regardless of how frustrating it can be for employees, this in no way excuses them to take matters into their own hands by disciplining and causing injury to someone else\'s child. A store clerk learned this lesson the hard way after she was arrested for simple battery for whipping an unruly 8-year-old boy who was misbehaving in the store.\r\n\r\nAccording to the police chief, store video surveillance and the boy himself, the clerk became angered after she attempted to stop the boy from running around in the store and he responded by throwing a cookie at her. She allegedly took him behind the counter and struck him on the back with her belt at least 25 times. After reviewing the store\'s video, the police chief wants to upgrade the woman\'s charge to aggravated assault.\r\n\r\nFor the safety of their children and others, parents have a responsibility to ensure they behave in public. But when another person takes over and causes child injury, the family has the right to pursue legal action.\r\n\r\n<strong>Source</strong>: The Huffington Post, \"<a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/02/04/emilia-graciela-bell-store-clerk-spanks-boy_n_2616222.html\" target=\"_blank\">Emilia Graciela Bell, Store Clerk, Allegedly Spanked \'Demon\' Boy, Logan Ivey, Who Wasn\'t Her Son</a>,\" Megan Griffo, Feb. 4, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Clerk arrested for battery, child injury, for spanking unruly kid', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'clerk-arrested-for-battery-child-injury-for-spanking-unruly-kid', '', '', '2014-02-28 07:45:27', '2014-02-28 07:45:27', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=902', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('903', '1', '2014-02-28 07:45:27', '2014-02-28 07:45:27', '<div>\r\n\r\nWe\'ve all had moments where we\'ve wished parents would control their children in public places. Not only are they an annoyance to others, but out-of-control kids can pose a danger to themselves and other people. Most businesses have policies in place that require parents to supervise their children while shopping. This prevents them or other customers from getting hurt by merchandise, hot foods or liquids or damaging property.\r\n\r\nIn some instances, the parents are unable to supervise or correct their misbehaving children. Regardless of how frustrating it can be for employees, this in no way excuses them to take matters into their own hands by disciplining and causing injury to someone else\'s child. A store clerk learned this lesson the hard way after she was arrested for simple battery for whipping an unruly 8-year-old boy who was misbehaving in the store.\r\n\r\nAccording to the police chief, store video surveillance and the boy himself, the clerk became angered after she attempted to stop the boy from running around in the store and he responded by throwing a cookie at her. She allegedly took him behind the counter and struck him on the back with her belt at least 25 times. After reviewing the store\'s video, the police chief wants to upgrade the woman\'s charge to aggravated assault.\r\n\r\nFor the safety of their children and others, parents have a responsibility to ensure they behave in public. But when another person takes over and causes child injury, the family has the right to pursue legal action.\r\n\r\n<strong>Source</strong>: The Huffington Post, \"<a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/02/04/emilia-graciela-bell-store-clerk-spanks-boy_n_2616222.html\" target=\"_blank\">Emilia Graciela Bell, Store Clerk, Allegedly Spanked \'Demon\' Boy, Logan Ivey, Who Wasn\'t Her Son</a>,\" Megan Griffo, Feb. 4, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Clerk arrested for battery, child injury, for spanking unruly kid', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '902-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-28 07:45:27', '2014-02-28 07:45:27', '', '902', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/902-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('904', '1', '2013-02-01 07:45:52', '2013-02-01 07:45:52', '<div>\r\n\r\nAdults entrusted with the care of a minor have a responsibility in making sure the child is safe while under their watch -- especially when the adult in question has a notable position of authority in the community. When the adult isn\'t the parent and knowingly places that child at risk of injury, serious legal consequences can result.\r\n\r\nWhen an off-duty Caroline County sheriff\'s deputy drove a teenage girl to a party, he didn\'t inform her parents that he knew she planned to drink alcohol that night. He continued to stay in touch with her via text messaging as she drank through the night until another party attendee texted to inform him that she was unconscious and not responding. After he returned to the home and failed to revive her, the deputy left without notifying the adults in the house, her parents, or law enforcement of what had happened.\r\n\r\nThe following morning, another person in the home called the deputy while he was on duty and told him the girl was still unconscious. He instructed the caller to call 911 but didn\'t respond to the emergency call himself. After hospitalization, the girl was found to have a blood alcohol content 6.5 times higher than the legal limit of an adult of drinking age.\r\n\r\nThe deputy now faces charges as a result of his negligence and irresponsible behavior. Facilitating the endangerment of a minor, failing to provide first responder medical assistance, concealing his involvement and the violation of the law as a sworn law enforcement officer, and putting the girl at risk of permanent injury are some of the many charges he is faced with.\r\n\r\nThe girl\'s parents may also wish to pursue legal action for compensation of their medical bills, and to ensure the officer is held accountable for his actions.\r\n\r\n<strong>Source</strong>: MyEasternShoreMD.com, \"<a href=\"http://www.myeasternshoremd.com/news/caroline_county/article_0381168c-6701-11e2-8f88-0019bb2963f4.html\" target=\"_blank\">Deputy faces endangerment allegation</a>,\" Abby Andrews, Jan. 25, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Caroline County cop in trouble for driving teen to drinking party', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'caroline-county-cop-in-trouble-for-driving-teen-to-drinking-party', '', '', '2014-02-28 07:46:47', '2014-02-28 07:46:47', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=904', '0', 'post', '', '0');
