INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('930', '1', '2013-11-24 09:44:31', '2013-11-24 09:44:31', '<div>\r\n\r\nIn many instances, proving that a medical physician is liable for negligence or misdiagnosis is only half the battle. Introducing a medical malpractice lawsuit can be a long and difficult process--one that doesn’t simply end at determining fault. The jury charged with ruling on a malpractice trial is often also responsible for deciding what the appropriate amount of damages owed to the victim/s is in the case. Failing to come to an agreement on damages can compromise the entire case in some instances. For example, a mistrial was recently called in a case where a Maryland jury was unable to agree on the damages to award to the victim.\r\n\r\nThe specific case in question is only one of hundreds filed against a prominent Maryland cardiologist. The trial, which was the first of its kind to result in a guilty verdict against the doctor, was also the first where the defendant himself testified. The other cases ended in settlements.\r\n\r\nWhile the cardiologist identified as the defendant in the medical malpractice lawsuit claims that he did his job, the plaintiff in the case accuses him of misdiagnosis and performing unnecessary stent surgery that resulted in the plaintiff sustaining emotional and medical complications, in addition to financial difficulties. Alleging that he was forced to end his career as a result of the surgery, the plaintiff requested $50 million in damages.\r\n\r\nThe mistrial was declared after jurors spent almost a week trying to determine how much the victim should receive in damages. The judge ruled that the jury could only find the hospital liable for damages, even though the doctor was found guilty of malpractice. Because of the mistrial, some experts believe another trial may be necessary to determine damages.\r\n\r\n<b>Source: </b>Baltimore Sun, “<a href=\"http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2013-11-06/health/bs-md-midei-trial-20131106_1_glenn-weinberg-mark-midei-jury-deadlocks\" target=\"_blank\">Mistrial in Midei stent case as jury deadlocks on damages</a>,” Jessica Anderson Nov. 6, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Inability to determine damages stalls medical malpractice suit', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'inability-to-determine-damages-stalls-medical-malpractice-suit', '', '', '2014-02-28 09:46:12', '2014-02-28 09:46:12', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=930', '0', 'post', '', '0');
