INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('944', '1', '2013-09-27 09:55:59', '2013-09-27 09:55:59', '<div>\r\n\r\nWhen a patient in Maryland undergoes routine procedure, there is usually no reason to worry. Routine procedures are performed on a regular bases and generally have very high success rates. In some cases, however, a rare accident can occur in the operating room.\r\n\r\nMercy Hospital St. Louis has issued a written statement saying the hospital will pursue an appeal in a medical negligence case involving a woman who died of complications following a routine procedure. The hospital stated that they took reasonable steps to attend to the patient. Attorneys for the plaintiffs’ alleged that when complications arose, the hospital did not act quickly enough. They argued that nearly 30 minutes passed before the woman was taken into surgery.\r\n\r\nThe 34-year-old mother of three died in February 2011 after she underwent a cardiac catheterization at the hospital. According to the family’s attorney, one of the woman’s coronary arteries was hit by the tip of the catheter during the routine procedure; as a result, less blood made it to her heart. A jury awarded $10.8 million in compensatory damages to the family of the woman, which is one of the largest medical negligence awards in history in the area.\r\n\r\nIf your loved one was injured or died due to medical professional negligence, you may be entitled to compensation. Compensatory damages cover the costs associated with the injury or death, including medical bills, lost wages, funeral expenses, and pain and suffering. For more information on how to file a medical malpractice lawsuit, you may want to contact an attorney.\r\n\r\n<b>Source: </b>St. Louis Post-Dispatch, “<a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/business/local/st-louis-county-jury-awards-million-medical-negligence-verdict/article_d6483b50-a5ff-545f-b2a1-577fd20ffe29.html\" target=\"_blank\">St. Louis County jury awards $10.8 million medical negligence verdict</a>,” Jim Doyle, Aug. 30, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Hospital found medically negligent, may pursue an appeal', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hospital-found-medically-negligent-may-pursue-an-appeal', '', '', '2014-02-28 09:57:09', '2014-02-28 09:57:09', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=944', '0', 'post', '', '0');
