INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('948', '1', '2013-09-12 09:58:30', '2013-09-12 09:58:30', '<div>\r\n\r\nBringing a baby home is a period of time where parents learn to adjust to new schedules, exciting milestones and no sleep. For some whose children are influenced by birth injuries caused by medical malpractice, the elements of medications, extensive treatments and overwhelming anxiety are added to an already stressful situation. Many times, parents of Maryland newborns are robbed of the experience of having a newborn because of the negligence of a medical professional that assisted in the birth or care of their newborn baby.\r\n\r\nAn 18-year-old woman in Minnesota is suing a University Hospital for medical malpractice after her son was born in the hospital. According to her claim, her son faces permanent physical and mental disabilities because of mistakes made during her delivery. She is asking the hospital for $200,000 to cover her baby’s medical costs.\r\n\r\nThe University rarely deals with medical malpractice cases regarding birth injuries and has only settled 18 of 50 over the last eight years. The University has never lost a malpractice case that has gone to trial rather than reaching a settlement between both parties. The current lawsuit includes claims from the mother that her baby endured a lack of oxygen to the brain during her delivery.\r\n\r\nAlthough the University may have an impressive record, this does not necessarily mean that the health care professionals involved in the delivery weren’t negligent with the woman and her son. Each case may need to be studied and reviewed in detail to determine how the injuries happened and who is responsible for the boy’s medical bills.\r\n\r\n<b>Source: </b>Minnesota Daily, “<a href=\"http://www.mndaily.com/university/research/medical/2013/09/04/u-sued-alleged-malpractice\" target=\"_blank\">U sued for alleged malpractice</a>,” Meghan Holden, September 4, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'University hospital faces rare malpractice lawsuit', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'university-hospital-faces-rare-malpractice-lawsuit', '', '', '2014-02-28 10:00:13', '2014-02-28 10:00:13', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=948', '0', 'post', '', '0');
