INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('954', '1', '2013-08-22 10:03:06', '2013-08-22 10:03:06', '<div>\r\n\r\nWhile wrong-site surgeries are rare, when they happen they can be extremely devastating for the patient. People who experience unnecessary surgeries in New Jersey may be subjected to additional medical bills, increased recovery time, and pain and suffering. When this happens, the surgeon or hospital staff may be blamed for the unthinkable error.\r\n\r\nA woman ended up getting more than she bargained for when she was admitted to Halifax Hospital Medical Center for surgery. She was suffering from leg pain due to vascular disease and signed a consent form to have vascular graft surgery performed on her left leg. When she woke up from surgery, however, she was asked to sign a consent form for a procedure that was already completed on her right leg.\r\n\r\nThe patient’s surgeon told her that given her medical history, the surgery was justified. In reality, however, this was simply a case of wrong-site surgery. Instead of admitting to the mistake, the surgeon tried to convince the woman that the right leg procedure was done on purpose. In a report, the surgeon admitted that he was thinking of himself during this conversation. He is no longer working at the hospital.\r\n\r\nThe vascular graft surgery was completed on both of the woman’s legs. A nurse anesthetist was the one who caught the doctor error. Fifteen days after the surgical mistake, the hospital reported the incident.\r\n\r\nIf you are the victim of hospital negligence, you may be entitled to compensation. You do not have to suffer in silence. A lawyer may be of assistance in this area.\r\n\r\n<b>Source: </b>Orlando Sentinel, “<a href=\"http://www.orlandosentinel.com/health/os-halifax-hospital-wrong-leg-20130815,0,1874175.story\" target=\"_blank\">Patient at Halifax Hospital had surgery on wrong leg</a>,” Marni Jameson, August 15, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Woman asked to sign consent form after wrong-site surgery', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'woman-asked-to-sign-consent-form-after-wrong-site-surgery', '', '', '2014-02-28 10:04:11', '2014-02-28 10:04:11', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=954', '0', 'post', '', '0');
