INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('960', '1', '2013-07-15 10:08:52', '2013-07-15 10:08:52', '<div>\r\n\r\nWe hear of surgical errors and hospital errors in the news all the time. It\'s not uncommon for mistakes to be made in Maryland hospitals that compromise the health and safety of their patients and result in medical malpractice lawsuits. Even worse, some mistakes can cost a person his or her life. What most people wouldn\'t expect, however, is for medical professionals to make a mistake about whether their patient is actually dead before making post-mortem procedures.\r\n\r\nWhen a New York woman was taken to the emergency room for a drug overdose at St. Joseph\'s Hospital Center in 2009, doctors pronounced her dead and informed her family. However, a nurse told the doctors the woman had been showing signs of recovering. Despite this knowledge, doctors obtained consent from the woman\'s family to remove her from life support and harvest her organs.\r\n\r\nThe woman showed several signs of still being alive, such as passing a reflex test, apparently breathing on her own, and moving her lips and tongue. Perhaps most disturbing was the doctors’ instructions to the nurse to give the woman a strong sedative before cutting into her to remove her organs--a procedure that would not be necessary on a dead person. The woman awoke just before doctors were about to begin the surgery to remove her organs.\r\n\r\nThe hospital was sanctioned but only fined $22,000, and the victim and her family didn’t sue the hospital for their grievous mistake. Sadly, the woman committed suicide due to depression in 2011.\r\n\r\nCurrently, a centralized system doesn’t exist that requires hospitals to report mistakes. Perhaps if hospitals were made accountable for such errors, standardized procedures and reporting systems would be created to prevent other patients from harm.\r\n\r\n<b>Source: </b>Yahoo! News, “<a href=\"http://news.yahoo.com/blogs/sideshow/patient-awoke-doctors-errantly-preparing-remove-her-organs-141547610.html\" target=\"_blank\">Patient awoke to doctors mistakenly preparing to remove her organs</a>,” Eric Pfeiffer, July 9, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Grave doctor error nearly resulted in removal of woman\'s organs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'grave-doctor-error-nearly-resulted-in-removal-of-womans-organs', '', '', '2014-02-28 10:12:07', '2014-02-28 10:12:07', '', '0', 'http://odelugo.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?p=960', '0', 'post', '', '0');
